            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/football-manager-2026">Football Manager 26</a> has launched into early access on PC, available to those who pre-order the game on that platform. For those on consoles or mobile, the game will become available to play a little later on the 4th November.</p>
<p>The beta was pushed back a few hours by developer Sports Interactive, <a href="https://x.com/FootballManager/status/1981394069147292039">so some final checks on the early access build</a> could be made, but as of writing those who drop £44.99 / 53,99€ / $53.99 can now play the game. It's available on Steam, the Epic Game Store, and the Windows Store. It'll be coming to PC Game Pass soon, alongside the Xbox release in November.</p>
<p>In this early release version of the game, you can hop into a single player career mode or an online career, all progress in both will of course carry over in the full release come November. The game has a revamped interface compared to previous entries in the series, as well as fresh UI, possession formations (not the supernatural kind), <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/football-manager-26-adds-the-womens-game-for-the-first-time-with-official-barclays-womens-super-league-inclusion">and women's teams</a>!</p>

