<p>The game also has a revamped manager creator, which allows players to really put those fine touches on the poor soul who'll be blamed for every lost game and subpar benching decision. <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/football-manager-26-will-finally-include-official-fifa-licensing-for-the-first-time-with-a-special-international-management-update-for-the-world-cup">Football Manager announced earlier this month that the series had partnered with Fifa in a multi-year deal</a>, which provides an official licence for big FIFA competitions to the game. This includes the FIFA World Cup 2026, in Canada, Mexico, and the USA.</p><p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/brace-yourselves-football-manager-fans-ive-played-a-day-of-fm26-and-its-going-to-take-a-lot-of-getting-used-to">We've played Football Manager 26, and it'll take some getting used to</a> for series fans. However, if you're sick of hearing about the game and want to see all these changes yourselves, the game currently has a 10% discount during the early access period. Why not buy it, and check it out?</p>

